title: Health Ministry Announces Vaccination Program
text: The Ministry of Health announced a new vaccination program targeting rural areas. The plan includes mobile clinics and free immunization for children under the age of five.

title: Miracle Toothpaste Grows Hair Overnight
text: A toothpaste brand went viral claiming their product could regrow hair overnight. Dermatologists quickly debunked the advertisement as false and misleading.

title: Aliens Spotted Over Statue of Liberty
text: A mysterious light appeared over the Statue of Liberty last night. Social media users claim it was an alien spaceship, although no official report has confirmed this.

title: Black Tea Reverses Aging Claims Blog
text: A blog post claims that drinking three cups of black tea before sleep can reverse aging. The post has no supporting peer-reviewed research and was flagged as misinformation.

title: Seaweed-Based Plastic Could Save Oceans
text: Researchers in Japan have developed a new biodegradable packaging material made from seaweed. The innovation is expected to reduce plastic waste in oceans significantly.

title: TikTok Influencer Predicts Dreams With Phone
text: A TikTok influencer claims that sleeping with your phone under your pillow allows the government to send messages into your dreams. No scientific basis exists for this claim.

title: ISS Completes 100,000th Orbit Milestone
text: The International Space Station has completed its 100,000th orbit around Earth, marking a historic milestone in human space exploration, according to NASA.

title: Pet Psychic Talks to Dogs With Crystal Collar
text: A self-proclaimed pet psychic went viral claiming she could talk to dogs using a crystal collar. Experts dismissed it as a hoax, calling it pseudoscience.

title: Global Literacy Rates Reach Record High
text: A recent UN report shows global literacy rates have reached an all-time high, particularly in developing countries due to increased access to digital education tools.
